{
  "stem": "4276.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I have some letters that my mother wrote to another person there who was not Jewish, and she asked him if it's possible to send him something to eat and things like that.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "He says, you have to do it through me because they will not put anything for Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we learned what was going there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was one corner where my mother would go every day, and that time I was with her and my uncle.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my brother supposedly saw her and was screaming through the window of the prison.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't hear anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "On the other side of the building, there were cars standing, [SIGHS] taking prisoners to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that time, he was gone.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, in the beginning, he was together with his professors from the high school and some friends.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know why the young boys were there, but somehow probably-- Now at that time, there was no Jewish camp anymore-- I mean, completely not Jewish.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Everything was together.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But about beginning of November, middle of November, was somebody wrote to us incognito-- because they were afraid to be caught-- that my brother is now building the first Jewish place for Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This was not a house.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This was not a barrack even.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was just under a-- just not even a hall.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was with-- I think that in the beginning, they had no roof or nothing-- just few sticks around the place.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And was-- he got dysentery.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he couldn't do certain things what they wanted him to do.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So he was-- he got beating.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then we got the telegram.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think you saw the telegram from Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
